The paper deals with an optimization problem that arises in several applications, including sparse recovery, semi-supervised learning, and signal processing, which are all topics in machine learning and data science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories. The paper also proposes an algorithm that is guaranteed to converge geometrically, which is a topic in numerical analysis, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a likely category as well. The paper also involves information theory and signal processing, which are topics in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal Processing), respectively.
